[1] Pacific Syndromic Surveillance System Weekly Bulletin W50 (9-15 Dec 2019)
Date: Sun 15 Dec 2019
Source: World Health Organization [abridged, edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/world/pacific-syndromic-surveillance-system-weekly-bulletin-syst-me-de-surveillance-131; https://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/PSSS%20W50%202019%20%289-15%20Dec%29.pdf


Other updates - measles:
- Kiribati reports its 1st case of measles, an 11 month old infant (https://www.rnz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/405799/kiribati-records-first-measles-case).

- Samoa: As of 18 Dec 2019, there have been 5424 cases since the outbreak started. There were 53 recorded cases in the previous 24 hours. There have been 77 related deaths, with one fatality in the last 24 hours. There are currently 121 measles cases who are in-patients at all health facilities. Admissions include 17 critically ill children in the intensive care unit/high dependency unit. The total number of measles cases admitted to all hospitals recorded for the outbreak to date is 1749 (Source: Health Emergency Operations Centre Situation Report No. 33, 19 Dec 2019).

- Tonga: As of 15 Dec 2019, there have been 564 confirmed or suspected cases since October 2019 (the beginning of the outbreak). Majority (90%) of the cases are from Tongatapu, the main island. Cases generally have been mild with 12 hospital admissions since the start of the outbreak; there have been no deaths reported. During the past week, there have been 14 new cases: 10 from Tongatapu and 4 from Vava'u. Mass vaccination campaign targeting 10- to 24-year-old individuals not immunized in the school program began on 17 Dec [2019] (Source: Tonga Ministry of Health Measles outbreak Situation report No. 10).

- Fiji reports 23 confirmed cases to date. All the cases are from the Central health division of Fiji, on the island of Viti-Levu (the main island). There have been no deaths reported. The Fiji Ministry of Health and Medical Services is conducting a mass vaccination campaign to end on 24 Dec 2019 (Source: Media release No. 16 http://www.health.gov.fj/?p=7859).

- American Samoa confirms a total of 10 measles cases reported to the American Samoa Department of Health. There have been no deaths reported (Situation report for 8-14 Dec 2019).

- New Zealand: There were 11 confirmed measles cases reported for week 50/2019, bringing the total to 2168 for the year to date, with 764 (35.2%) hospitalisations. There are 2 ongoing outbreaks (Source: ESR, NZ https://surv.esr.cri.nz/surveillance/WeeklyMeaslesRpt.php?we_objectID=5061).

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[Kiribati, officially the Republic of Kiribati, is a country in the central Pacific Ocean. The permanent population is just over 110 000, more than half of whom live on Tarawa atoll. The state comprises 32 atolls and one raised coral island, Banaba (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kiribati).]

