[2] Samoa: Another child dies
Date: Wed 18 Dec 2019
Source: Stuff [abridged, edited]
https://www.stuff.co.nz/world/south-pacific/118302956/samoa-measles-outbreak-another-child-dies-from-measles


Another preschooler has been added to the measles death toll in Samoa overnight. The latest death comes the day after 2 children under the age of 5 died of the disease; the toll is now 76.

The Samoan Ministry of Health also confirmed 40 new measles cases were diagnosed in the last 24 hours. The number of new cases and deaths has slowed over the past week, with the Pacific nation's mass vaccination campaign starting to make an impact.

Earlier this month [December 2019], the Samoan Government ordered a nation-wide shutdown of the private and public sector to allow vaccinators to go to every home in their bid to immunise every person in the country.

Latest figure[s] show that 94% of the Samoan population have been vaccinated.

[Byline: Florence Kerr]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

