[7] Colorado
Date: Wed 18 Dec 2019
Source: Express [abridged, edited]
https://www.express.co.uk/news/world/1218555/measles-outbreak-warning-illness-virus-disease-death-Denver-Airport-colorado-California


It is thought the highly contagious virus [measles] could have affected those who used Denver International Airport. Three unidentified children are receiving treatment at Children's Hospital Colorado, having contracted the disease while abroad, according to a statement released by the Tri-County Health Department.

The children are related, according to The Denver Post, and they had not received the vaccine for measles, mumps or rubella before falling ill.

[See source URL for locations and times of possible exposure.]

The news comes on the same day health officials in California warned about a potential exposure from patients who travelled through Los Angeles International Airport.

A press release from officials read: "All individuals travelling on the plane with these children or who visited Children's Hospital Colorado during this time frame and are believed to be at risk and are being contacted directly by public health."

[Byline: Jacque Talbot]

